Floor 16: JS Strings and String Methods
D: "Strings are text in JavaScript, and we can manipulate them in many ways using built-in methods!"

D: "Common String Methods:\n• .length → Finds the number of characters in a string.\n• .toUpperCase() / .toLowerCase() → Changes case.\n• .slice(start, end) → Extracts a part of a string.\n• .replace("old", "new") → Replaces text."

=> END

